channel.title: I FORGOT my password for my router. Is that a problem?
channel.description:
Well, I was going to put a server up but when I tried to get on my router I forgot my password. Do I have to log in to direct my router?? I just plain need help. Becuase if I don't no my password that means I can't make a server? I use Hamachi but apperently I don't get enough people. If someone helps me they'll be an admin on my server.
So can someone please help!!!

item.title: I FORGOT my password for my router. Is that a problem?
item.dc:creator: @Aftermath_961 Aftermath
item.description:
@Aftermath_961 wrote:

Look on the back of your router, there should be a little circle the size of a pinhole. There should be a little button somewhere deeper in there. Get a paperclip, pencil, or pen and push that button for about 15 seconds. The password’ll be reset and you can find out what the original password for your router was at http://www.phenoelit.de/dpl/dpl.html, just google for the make of your router, it should be written on the top.
